.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBcancel_monitor(MRef) -> boolean() when MRef :: reference().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Cancel a socket monitor.

.PP
If \fIMRef\fR is a reference that the calling process obtained by calling \fImonitor/1\fR, this monitor is removed. If the monitoring is already removed, nothing happens.

.PP
The returned value is one of the following:

true
.RS 2
The monitor was found and removed. In this case, no 
\fI'DOWN'\fR message corresponding to this monitor has been delivered and will not be delivered.

.RE

false
.RS 2
The monitor was not found and couldn't be removed. Probably because the monitor has already triggered and there is a corresponding 
\fI'DOWN'\fR message in the caller message queue.

