\fB\fI{exclusiveaddruse, Boolean}\fR\fR  - Enables/disables exclusive address/port usage on Windows. That is, by enabling this option you can prevent other sockets from binding to the same address/port.  By default this option is disabled. That is, other sockets may use the same address/port by setting \fI{reuseaddr, true}\fR in combination with \fI{reuseport, true}\fR unless \fI{exclusiveaddruse, true}\fR has been set on \fISocket\fR. On non-Windows systems this option is silently ignored.

