\fIbinary\fR was specified when the socket was created. If option \fIheader\fR is specified, the first \fISize\fR number bytes of data received from the socket are elements of a list, and the remaining data is a binary specified as the tail of the same list. For example, if \fISize == 2\fR, the data received matches \fI[Byte1, Byte2 | Binary]\fR.

